				<td width="50%" valign="top"><span class="press-title">Indonesian Students Bring Papua’s Cultures to Singapore</span><br>
					<img src="http://www.globalindonesianvoices.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Nuansa.png" width="100%"><br>
					<p>Singapore, GIVnews.com – Every year, about 120 students in the National University of Singapore (NUS) are busy preparing for the biggest student production in campus: NUANSA Cultural Productions. It is an annual show which was started as a humble initiative in 2008 by a group of Indonesian students in NUS, aiming to showcase the diverse and rich Indonesian culture to the Singaporean community. Each show would feature a distinct culture from a region of Indonesia, complemented with mesmerizing songs and dance numbers originally created by NUANSA’s very own artistic team. Through its seven-year journey, NUANSA has significantly grown higher and higher in terms of production quality and audience outreach. <a href="http://www.globalindonesianvoices.com/22197/indonesian-students-bring-papuas-cultures-to-singapore/" target="_blank">Read more...</a></p></td>
				<td width="50%"><span class="press-title">Venturing Into New Territory: Behind the Scenes of NUANSA 2015</span><br>
					<img src="http://studentry.sg/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Article-1-Photo-3-Body-paint-resized-min.jpg" width="100%"><br>
					<p>It’s not easy to plan and conceptualise a theatre production, let alone one that centers on a culture that is not well known. Add to that the task of running a wholly student-run production involving 107 undergraduates, and you get NUANSA 2015: Flowers of Asmat. Launched in 2008, NUANSA is an annual arts and cultural production organised by a group of Indonesian students in PINUS, with the aim of showcasing the richness and diversity of Indonesian culture. With less than a week before NUANSA 2015, our writer Ignatius Albert gives us an exclusive access to their rehearsal, to find out more about the story behind the play. <a href="http://studentry.sg/2015/09/28/nuansa-2015-bts-1/" target="_blank">Read more...</a></p></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td width="50%" valign="top"><span class="press-title">Mahasiswa Indonesia Gelar Pementasan Seni di NUS Singapura</span><br>
					<img src="img/press/news1.jpg" width="100%"><br>
					<p>Singapura, Kemdikbud --- Kementerian Pendidikan dan Kebudayaan melalui kegiatan Rumah Budaya Indonesia di Singapura menjadi sponsor utama pergelaran Nuansa. Pergelaran Nuansa, singkatan dari NUS dan Indonesia, merupakan karya Perhimpunan Pelajar Indonesia di salah satu universitas di Singapura, National University of Singapore (NUS). <a href="http://www.kemdiknas.go.id/kemdikbud/berita/3328" target="_blank">Read more...</a></p></td>
				<td width="50%"><span class="press-title">NUANSA Cultural Production in Singapore Attracts 1280 Audiences with The Priyayi</span><br>
					<img src="img/press/news2.jpg" width="100%"><br>
					<p>GIVnews.com – Tickets for NUANSA’14: The Priyayi, a cultural production by Indonesian students in the National University of Singapore, were sold out two weeks in advance before the show on 6 October 2014. The third level of the University Cultural Centre Hall must even be opened, the first time in NUANSA seven-years run, to accommodate the overwhelming public enthusiasm. <a href="http://www.globalindonesianvoices.com/16331/nuansa-cultural-production-in-singapore-attracts-1280-audiences-with-the-priyayi/" target="_blank">Read more...</a></p></td>
			</tr><tr>
