				<td><span class="press-title">Pelajar Indonesia di Singapura Sukses Pentaskan "Dance of the Earth"</span><br>
					<img src="img/press/news3.jpg" width="100%"><br>
					<p>SINGAPURA, KOMPAS.com - Pelajar Indonesia di National University of Singapore (NUS) mengadaptasi novel Tarian Bumi (Dance of the Earth) menjadi drama musikal yang menawan selama hampir dua jam.</p>
					<p>Tak kurang dari 1.200 penonton yang tak hanya pelajar, tapi juga pekerja profesional, hingga warga asing dari berbagai negara memenuhi University Cultural Centre, Minggu malam (6/10/2013). <a href="http://edukasi.kompas.com/read/2013/10/07/0905042/Pelajar.Indonesia.di.Singapura.Sukses.Pentaskan.Dance.of.the.Earth" target="_blank">Read more...</a></p></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="press-title">Nuansa 2011: Indonesian students in Singapore retrace Old Batavia legend</span><br>
					<p>Ten long months of preparation paid off as the audience broke into thunderous applause, filling the theater at the Anglo Chinese Junior College.</p>
					<p>This was the curtain call of NUANSA 2011, Ca Bau Kan, The Musical, which took place on Oct. 22. With back-to-back performances, the musical was attended by a total of 894 audiences. Tickets for the evening show had been sold out for more than a month in advance. <a href="http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2011/11/20/nuansa-2011-indonesian-students-singapore-retrace-old-batavia-legend.html#sthash.Uqp8o2FQ.dpuf" target="_blank">Read more...</a></p></td>
